page.title: 02LANDSCAPE NEAR LISBURN
page.content: _The Lisburn to Glenavy Road almost bisects this D_block from S.E. to N.W. On the northerly side of this road the land is much higher and is all over 130m above sea level.Here there are few trees.To the south of the road,in the lower_lying areas,there are several substantial farms on what were formerly large country estates belonging to landed_gentry and here there are more trees. .Overall,however,the landscape consists of a pattern of grassland fields,usually separated by hedges.
